# Delight UX

See also: **`interaction-polish.mdc`** (feedback, motion, consistency), **`error-handling.mdc`** (empty states must still teach), **`design-tokens.mdc`**, **`accessibility.mdc`**, **`performance.mdc`**.

**Delight** = small moments of personality that turn a **functional** state into something **memorable**. Use **sparingly** on screens where extra warmth earns trust — not as default chrome on every page.

This rule does **not** replace polish, empty-state guidance, or accessibility. Delight sits **on top** when the moment warrants it.

## When delight fits

| Moment | Example |
| ------ | ------- |
| **Milestone / achievement** | “100 tasks completed”, first publish, streak |
| **Onboarding completion** | Welcome done → first real screen |
| **Positive empty → first success** | First item created after an intentional empty state |
| **Rare positive surprise** | Long-awaited export finished, invite accepted |

The user should feel **rewarded**, not marketed at.

## When delight does not fit

| Moment | Why |
| ------ | --- |
| Errors, auth failures, payments | Recovery and clarity only — **`error-handling.mdc`** |
| Loading / skeletons | Acknowledge work — no jokes while waiting |
| Dense dashboards, settings, tables | Information throughput wins — **`interaction-polish.mdc`** |
| Every section header or CTA | Becomes noise; feels like a template |
| Critical compliance / legal flows | Neutral, precise copy |

**Default:** ship functional + polished. Add delight only when you can name the **specific moment** worth celebrating.

## Design constraints (still required)

- **Semantic tokens only** — `text-warning`, `text-success`, `text-primary`, `bg-muted/30`; no raw `amber-500`, `gold`, or hex (`design-tokens.mdc`).
- **Typography scale** — `text-sm` / `text-lg` / `text-4xl`; no arbitrary `text-[72px]`.
- **Motion** — short, optional; respect `prefers-reduced-motion` (`interaction-polish.mdc`, `index.css`).
- **Accessibility** — celebration text is **visible copy**, not emoji alone; use `role="status"` + `aria-live="polite"` for one-shot milestones; do not trap focus or block the next action.

```tsx
// Bad — decoration without meaning; arbitrary color; blocks workflow
<div className="text-[#f59e0b] text-[80px]">🎉🎉🎉</div>

// Good — milestone panel; semantic tokens; user can dismiss or continue
<section
  role="status"
  aria-live="polite"
  className="flex flex-col items-center gap-2 rounded-lg border border-border bg-muted/30 px-6 py-8 text-center"
>
  <p className="text-sm font-medium tracking-wide text-warning uppercase">
    Milestone unlocked
  </p>
  <p className="text-4xl font-semibold tabular-nums text-foreground">100</p>
  <p className="text-sm text-muted-foreground">tasks completed</p>
  <Button className="mt-4 w-full sm:w-auto" onClick={onContinue}>
    Keep going
  </Button>
</section>
```

Emoji or icons are **optional garnish** — one line max; never the only message.

## Copy tone

- **Short** — headline + number or fact + one line of context.
- **Specific** — “100 tasks completed”, not “Amazing job superstar!!!”.
- **Forward-looking** — hint the next step (“Keep going”, “Create your next item”).
- **Match product voice** — warm ≠ loud; avoid forced puns on every screen.

## Implementation patterns

| Pattern | Use |
| ------- | --- |
| **Inline panel** | Milestone on the page that earned it (not a blocking modal unless product requires) |
| **Toast** | Light acknowledgment after a small win — supplement, not replace UI update |
| **One-time flag** | `localStorage` / user prefs so the same milestone does not replay every visit |
| **Colocated component** | `MilestoneCelebration.tsx` next to the feature — not global confetti |

Do not add animation libraries for delight alone; CSS transitions or existing primitives are enough.

## Relationship to other rules

| Rule | Division |
| ---- | -------- |
| `error-handling.mdc` | Empty/error **must** teach and recover — delight may soften **positive** empty-to-first-win only |
| `interaction-polish.mdc` | All interactions acknowledged; delight is **extra**, not a substitute for loading/error UX |
| `page-layout.mdc` | Delight panels follow zone rhythm — do not break shell alignment for a one-off |
| `feature-state.mdc` | Derive `showMilestone` from data + one-time flag — no extra boolean soup in JSX |

## Checklist (when adding delight)

- [ ] Named moment — milestone, first success, or onboarding complete (not “because we can”).
- [ ] Not on error, payment, auth failure, or blocking load.
- [ ] Semantic tokens and type scale only; motion respects reduced motion.
- [ ] Copy + structure accessible; emoji is decorative, not the only label.
- [ ] User can proceed immediately — delight does not block the primary path.
- [ ] Shown once (or rarely), not on every repeat visit.
